The paper discusses the use of Grey Literature (GL) in software engineering research, which involves synthesizing knowledge from various sources such as trade magazines, online blog-posts, survey results, and technical reports. This topic is closely related to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE), as well as information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL) which deal with the organization and retrieval of information. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential benefits of GL for human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) research, which are also relevant sub-categories.
